Missale of Count Novak - Misal kneza Novaka

This is a page about the Missale of Count Novak. Here you find a transcription of this text in a critical and a simplified version.

Missale of Count Novak - Misal kneza Novaka

edited by

Kristijan Kuhar / Ivan Botica / Silvio Košćak / Sandra Požar / Andrea Radošević / Erich Renhart

Old Church Slavonic Institute, Zagreb and Vestigia, Graz

Zagreb - Graz

03.10.2022

Vienna, Vienna National Library: Cod. Slav. 8

The facsimile of the manuscript is available via the Austrian National Library

Form: codex

Material: parchment

Extent: 32 cm x 24 cm

Layout: Written surface of 205 mm x 75 mm with 32 lines per column (2 columns per page).

Decoration: Contains coloured capitals and decoration.

Date: Written in the 14th century: 1368

11srêdê skr’bi živiši me g(ospod)i . na

12gnêvь vragь moih’ prostrê ruk

13u tvoû i sp(a)si me desnica tvoê .

[left column]super oblata



13 (cont.)rubrica minor N(a)d /prinošenie/ .

14V’ tvoih’ g(ospod)i semr’ti prav’dn

15nihь . žr’tvu onu pr(ê)krasnu

16û prinosimь ot koe muki vsakь

17priêtь začelo .

[left column]communio
